AMR Corp's American Airlines unit saidit plans to complete the integration of AirCal into itsoperations within four to five months.    American's merger with AirCal, announced last November,received final approval from the Department of Transportationyesterday.    American said Richard D. Pearson, coordinator of theairline's merger activities, will become chairman and chiefexecutive officer of AirCal during the period up to completionof the merger.    American said Pearson succeeds William Lyon, who has beenelected to AMR's board.    It added that David A. Banmiller will continue as AirCal'spresident and chief operating officer. Reuter&#3;